    divisorFound = true;
  }
}
System.out.println(1);
if (!divisorFound) {
  System.out.println(&quot;relatively prime&quot;);
}
```

Of course, there are more efficient algorithms. For instance, one could use [euklid&#39;s algorithm](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Euclidean_algorithm) to efficiently determine the greatest common divisor, then find its prime factors, and use that to efficiently iterate all divisors. 

